FISH 274

Introduction

This presentation shows the size and locations for visible

Hippocampus reidi populations off the coast of Brazil. Its

purpose is to help snorkelers and scuba divers who want to

view seahorses in the wild. The data will compare the size

and population trends of the locations.

Locations in Brazil sampled for Hippocampus reidi

  • Camurupim
  • Ubatuba
  • Pacoti
  • Mal Cozinhado
  • Tubaro
  • Casqueira
  • Mamanguape
  • Itapessoca
  • Ariquind
  • Andorinhas
  • Itaipu
  • Penha

The range of Hippocampus reidi is Cape Hatteras, United States to Brazil and the Gulf of Mexico

How to Find Them

Image of Hippocampus reidi

Hippocampus reidi can

be found down to 55

meters and can grow

to approximately 17.5

centimeters long. They

are found in coral

reefs and seagrass

beds.

Video of Hippocampus reidi

Also known as the

longsnout seahorse

males and females are

easily distinguished

due to their bright

colors.

Conclusion

Casqueira had both the highest visible population and the

largest average size. The largest overall popluations and

average sizes occured along the northern coast of Brazil.

Being a small coastline compared to the eastern side of

Brazil it would be a good idea to stay north if your goal

is to see Hippocampus reidi in the wild.
